{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01257kQ23Dvmvyhxc2ibxUzX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Elasticsearch cluster uses HTTP (not HTTPS internally), since `xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false`. \n\nNow I need to:\n1. Generate a self-signed TLS certificate for `es.example.com`\n2. Create a Kubernetes secret with that TLS cert in the elasticsearch namespace\n3. Create an Ingress resource with:\n   - TLS termination at the ingress\n   - HTTPS-only (redirect HTTP to HTTPS or block it)\n   - Route to `es-http:9200`\n   - Use the `nginx` ingress class\n\nLet me generate a self-signed certificate and create the ingress.\nI'll use openssl to create the self-signed cert for es.example.com, then create a TLS secret in the elasticsearch namespace. For the Ingress, I'll configure it with the nginx ingress class, TLS termination using that secret, and add the ssl-redirect annotation to force HTTPS. I'm still considering whether \"should not succeed\" means redirecting HTTP to HTTPS or rejecting it outright. One approach is to use the standard `ssl-redirect` annotation, which redirects HTTP requests to HTTPS with a 308 response—technically the HTTP request doesn't succeed in accessing the API content. Alternatively, I could configure separate ingress resources to strictly reject HTTP without redirecting, but the redirect approach is cleaner and more standard for Kubernetes nginx ingress.\n\nI'll go with the SSL redirect method and generate the certificate along with the necessary resources.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":765,"cache_read_input_tokens":31285,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":765},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1aecf9ff-65e3-42e2-b85e-8d0f09abc05d","uuid":"761d3191-163d-418f-b10b-52dc5b0cf389","request_id":"req_011CbzGgcDcNV4yVjmQq7jMk"}
